Faceawards India 2019 Link IN BIO
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
HEY GUYS ♥️ This is my submission for the final round of @nyxcosmetics_in Faceawards 2019
"Wonderland After Dark"
 Please support me by voting if you like my work🥰 This video is very close to my heart💖
.
 " You're entirely bonkers. But I'll tell you a secret.All the best people are." - Alice
.
Natural instinct of a being is to seek happiness. However due to world pressures and influences one gets trapped into the darkness of their own thoughts. This is symbolized by trapping of character into the the bottle of her own mind. When someone follows their own instincts and accepts the madness of their thoughts we keep moving forward opening new doors and doing new things because we are curious and curiosity keeps leading us down to new paths. 
i created the two looks to portray that there is a wonderland after dark if you believe in yourself.
.
Hope you like the looks I created ♥️
(please share with your friends and family each vote counts!❤) so be sure to comeback to vote!
THANK YOU SO MUCH IN ADVANCE ❤️ Video was produced and edited by self

latestIgtvVideos.title: NYX FACEAWARDS 2019 TOP15-EMOTIONS❤LINK IN BIO
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This is so close to my heart. I feel with these characters I am able to tell tiny part of my story and emotions❤ 
.
For this challenge I created two looks to potray emotions in daily life and how we mask them in front of others.How we stop ourselves from portraying multiple emotions that are inside us. The first look reveals  how one fears and suppresses emotions which has led to numbness whereas taking down the mask in second look she has let her boundaries down letting herself feel and be free.

Be on a lookout on my page,i will be sharing everything about the looks throughout the week with details.

p.s video produced and edited by self❤️

latestPosts.caption:
Tips to stay inspired during the holiday season 🎄💫 As a makeup content creator sometimes it can be difficult to stay inspired or always be at your creative best. So here’s a little peak into my creative processes🎄💫
Finding inspiration and drawing looks is usually my first step of creating videos, which eliminates any pressure during days when filming feels like a hastle. 
Let me know if this helped in any way and if we should do more of these 🤍✨

Grinch bombs from @homesensecanada 🎄
@yslbeauty loveshine lipstick in love berry

#artisticmakeup #makeuphacks #contentcreationtips

Part 5: Spend a day in creative advertising working as a content creator 📸 Hi! if you’re new here I shoot videos, create brand content for socials, experiment with makeup, keep looking for inspo & paint my face if that inspires me. We also try to balance this sometimes to keep the creative spark or just completely rot in bed until the spark comes back 🤓 

#creativeprocess #pinterest #marketing #torontocontentcreator

Reminder incase you needed today🫶🏻 Being present is the way you can create things that feel true to self, sometimes when you slow down you notice more & when you notice more, you make better art ✨ 

[sow days, in the moment, creative recharge, creative artist]

Another day of our art projects 🎨 The blue ceramics were a sign 🤓 It made me think of Kintsugi, the Japanese technique of mending what’s broken with gold or silver, so of course we turned it into makeup.

#avantegardemakeup #kintsugi #artisticprocess #torontocreatives

Inspired by the Japanese, Kintsugi art 🦋 The art of repairing broken pottery with gold or silver lacquer! 
I have seen many beautiful recreations of this art and I wanted to do one of my own 🔹
